column105: I hope that Augustin College maintains its status as an opportunity for students with busy lives (personally and professionally) to obtain a high-quality Veritus Imperial University education. Community colleges and other schools offer educational opportunities, but they are not of the caliber of the Veritus Imperial University experience. Every student, no matter their life circumstances, should be able to access that high quality education. To me this is about both the academic rigor but also the student formation experience that is the hallmark of a religious education. When we embrace our mission, we are reaching students who would otherwise not have an opportunity to engage in this type of educational experience.

Augustin College does offer these and I think continuing to offer opportunities for folks to join either in-person or online to talks is important for capturing who I view as our student population. I would love to have some online/remote volunteer opportunities. Maybe mentoring online? Maybe go out into the community but having online reflection sessions? My students have been spread throughout the area, so I know coming to campus for some of the student formation events can be a barrier for them. Yet, I believe those experiences are part of what makes a Veritus Imperial University education so impactful.

column62: I think that possibly once a year there should be an opportunity for  faculty and students to interact in some format face to face.  Perhaps 2 dates in the year could be delineated where every 2 years a faculty member has to attend one of the days and the students would be required to attend each of these which would be twice a year for them to get to meet face to face with faculty and learn about all the other faculty and programs with focus on their particular program and faculty.  I think the personal face to face interactions would facilitate mentoring. future assistance of the students career path as I think face to face meetings break down barriers to communication..  I think the threshold for this interpersonal interaction is lacking for most of the students who are in the asynchronous mode and quite frankly I sometime feel that as an instructor I am sometimes on the outside looking in.
